# 🧠 NeuralCode — AI-Powered Coding Mentor

> Final Year Project | B.Tech Computer Science & Engineering
> An AI coding tutor for absolute beginners powered by Groq (Llama 3.3) + Node.js + MongoDB

---

## 🌟 Live Demo
🔗 **[neuralcode.vercel.app](https://neuralcode.vercel.app)**

---

## ✨ Features

| Feature | Description |
|---|---|
| 🔐 **Auth System** | Register, login, logout with JWT and bcrypt |
| 🤖 **AI Mentor Chat** | 4 modes — Explain, Debug, Challenge, ELI5 |
| 🎯 **AI Quiz Generator** | Dynamic quizzes generated fresh every session |
| 🔍 **AI Code Reviewer** | Score, grade and feedback on your code |
| 🗺️ **Learning Roadmap** | Step-by-step JavaScript curriculum |
| ⚡ **XP and Gamification** | Points, levels, streaks, achievements |
| 📱 **Fully Responsive** | Works on mobile, tablet and desktop |
| 🗄️ **MongoDB Database** | All user data persisted in the cloud |

---

## 🛠️ Tech Stack

| Layer | Technology |
|---|---|
| Frontend | HTML5, CSS3, Vanilla JavaScript |
| Backend | Node.js, Express.js |
| Database | MongoDB Atlas with Mongoose |
| AI Engine | Groq API — Llama 3.3 70B |
| Auth | JWT jsonwebtoken + bcryptjs |
| Deployment | Vercel |

---

## 📁 Project Structure

```
neuralcode/
├── server.js          ← Express backend (auth + AI proxy routes)
├── package.json       ← Node dependencies
├── .env               ← Environment variables (never commit this)
├── .gitignore         ← Files excluded from Git
├── README.md          ← This file
└── Public/
    └── index.html     ← Complete frontend single page app
```

---

## 🚀 Local Setup

### Prerequisites
- Node.js v18 or higher
- MongoDB Atlas free account
- Groq API key from console.groq.com (free)

### Step 1 — Clone the repo
```bash
git clone https://github.com/YOURNAME/neuralcode.git
cd neuralcode
```

### Step 2 — Install dependencies
```bash
npm install
```

### Step 3 — Create .env file
```env
GROQ_API_KEY=your_groq_api_key_here
MONGO_URI=mongodb+srv://username:password@cluster.mongodb.net/neuralcode
JWT_SECRET=your_secret_key_here
PORT=3001
```

### Step 4 — Run the server
```bash
node server.js
```

### Step 5 — Open in browser
```
http://localhost:3001
```

---

## 🌐 Deploy to Vercel

```bash
git add .
git commit -m "deploy"
git push
```

Then go to vercel.com, import your repo and add these environment variables:
- GROQ_API_KEY
- MONGO_URI
- JWT_SECRET

---

## 🔐 Security Features

- Passwords hashed with bcrypt cost factor 12
- JWT tokens expire after 7 days
- All AI routes require valid authentication
- Groq API key stored server-side only, never exposed to browser
- MongoDB injection blocked by input validation regex
- CORS configured for cross-origin requests

---

## 📊 API Endpoints

| Method | Route | Auth Required | Description |
|---|---|---|---|
| POST | /auth/register | No | Create new account |
| POST | /auth/login | No | Login and get JWT token |
| GET | /auth/me | Yes | Get current user data |
| PATCH | /user/progress | Yes | Save XP and progress |
| POST | /api/chat | Yes | Get AI mentor response |
| POST | /api/quiz | Yes | Generate quiz questions |
| POST | /api/review | Yes | Review submitted code |

---

## 🤖 AI Chat Modes

| Mode | Behaviour |
|---|---|
| Explain | Beginner analogies with code examples |
| Debug | Find bugs and explain fix in plain English |
| Challenge | Generate achievable beginner coding tasks |
| ELI5 | Explain Like I am 5 using everyday analogies |

